terms.medium_def:
An angel in the Old Testament; 
called Satan or "accuser" (KJV= Satan) (שָׂטָן); or "worthless" (KJV= Belial; NIV= "troublemakers") or "worthless" (KJV= Belial; NIV= "wicked") or "worthless" (KJV= Belial; NIV= "evil") or "worthless" (KJV= Belial; NIV= "scoundrel") or "scoundrel" (KJV= Belial) (בְּלִיַּ֫עַל); or Beelzebul (KJV= Beelzebub) (Βεελζεβούλ); or Belial (Βελίαλ); or Satan (Σατάν); or [ ] (KJV= Satan) or Satan (Σατανᾶς) §
This name means worthless, base, wicked
